  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD pipeline employs a multi-physics solver stack (OpenFOAM-based hemolysis module, Python post-processing scripts, and a parallel MPI execution layer). Solver robustness was studied informally during development; no systematic exercise of software-fault modes — such as NaN propagation under extreme shear-rate inputs, race conditions in parallel mesh decomposition, or edge-case crashes at low-flow operating points — was performed or documented. All validation runs completed to nominal termination.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
