      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used in the simulation is developed and maintained under a documented quality management process appropriate for MRL 2, with version control and basic regression testing.",
      "rationale": "OpenFOAM-based hemolysis solver and Python post-processing scripts are maintained under version control (Git) with a documented release process. Unit regression tests cover core fluid solver routines. Software quality is assessed as meeting Gradation 2 requirements. Note: systematic testing for software fault modes such as race conditions in parallel execution, numerical instability under extreme boundary conditions, or edge-case exception handling was conducted informally during development and is not documented in the formal SQA record. No fault-injection or robustness metrics are available."
