      "rationale": "Bench hemolysis experiments performed at 5 flow-speed operating points (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Fluid temperature, hematocrit, and inlet/outlet pressures documented. Blood analog fluid (porcine blood, standardized hematocrit 35%) used consistently across test matrix. Environmental conditions recorded within ISO 15223 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison between simulation outputs and experimental measurements using appropriate metrics; agreement within defined acceptance bounds.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index predictions compared against bench measurements using normalized index of hemolysis (NIH). Mean absolute percentage error across 5 operating points is 12.4%, within the 15% acceptance bound established for MRL 2. PIV velocity field comparison shows average normalized RMS error of 8.7% in the impeller region."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation are directly relevant to the clinical decision being supported; relative hemolysis index is an accepted surrogate for in vivo hemolysis performance.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary QoI and directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device). Secondary QoIs include NIH and velocity field statistics. These quantities are established in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device CFD submissions and are appropriate for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
